The world No 85 rallied from a set down to beat Lithuania's Ricardas Berankis 4-6, 6-3, 6-1. Harris showed a lot of determination and fighting spirit to advance to the second round where he will face Great Britain's Kyle Edmund on Tuesday. Fourth seeded South African Kevin Anderson is also in action at the Washington Open and he will open his campaign against Frenchman Adrian Mannarino on Wednesday. In doubles, South Africa's Raven Klaasen and his New Zealand partner Michael Venus are the third seeds. They open their campaign on Wednesday against German duo Andreas Mies and Kevin Krawietz.

